            <scopecontent id="aspace_29e940649a13cb138017cbe9924ee5c9">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The James L. Livingston Family Papers consist of bills, receipts, and a few miscellaneous papers of the Livingston household of Lawrence, Long Island, principally dating from the first decade of the twentieth century. The bills and receipts give some vivid impressions of upper-class life and furnish a little information about the wages of local service workers. The principal family members are James LaRhett Livingston, who died in 1907, and his wife, Frances Park (Forsyth) Livingston, originally from Philadelphia.</p>
            </scopecontent>
